profile:
I had been in the Winnipeg electrical services industry for 13 years, before deciding to start my own business, John Doerksen Electrical, which has been around since 2011.

My early electrical training was primarily done by skilled union members, but I have since moved into the non-union member sector. While in the union sector, my experience consisted mostly of commercial electrical and industrial electrical.

I have been trained in electrical services including:

Fibre Optics
Data
Residential electrical
Commercial electrical
Industrial wiring and electrical
As a local Winnipeg resident, my dream was to own a business, which would allow me to provide for my family. Having always been interested and naturally talented at electrical systems, becoming a Winnipeg electrician seemed like a logical next step.

I know what electricians in Winnipeg cost. My goal was to provide Winnipeg homeowners with safe and affordable electrical services.

I pride myself on being honest and reliable, and my current and past customers can attest to that.

With John Doerksen Electrical, you get personalized service at a fair price. My workmanship is warrantied, as my reputation goes hand in hand with my success as a business.

I also provide free quotes and 24/7 emergency services.
